      <!-- BARINGS BANK -->
      <article class="event" id="event-barings">
        <header>
          <h3><time datetime="1995">1995</time> — Barings Bank</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          Nick Leeson was simultaneously executing trades and reporting on them
          from Barings' Singapore office — a fundamental separation-of-duties
          failure. He was also generating implausibly consistent profits that
          should have raised immediate questions about how. Nobody in London's
          management asked mechanistic questions. The dashboard — growing
          profits, a star trader — was too comfortable to interrogate. Barings
          lost £827 million, more than its entire capital, and collapsed in
          1995. It was Britain's oldest merchant bank, established 1762.
        </p>
